&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The difference you will make&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Staff Fullstack Engineer to serve as a technical pillar within our Engineering Org. As we scale, you will be a hands-on technical driver, distilling complex understanding from across Midi into cohesive technical roadmaps and products that help us revolutionize women&#39;s healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze complex technical problems and lead architectural reviews across multiple teams to prevent technical debt, establish cross-service patterns, and ensure the long-term sustainability of Midi’s healthcare ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a &#39;part-time product manager for technology,&#39; advocating for critical infrastructure upgrades that enable future business velocity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craft exceptional, thoughtful, scalable and flexible products and code, balancing for speed of execution and scalability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively shape engineering culture by establishing best practices for automated testing, CI/CD, and high-quality code across the entire stack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze high-level technical and business problems and architect elegant, flexible solutions that account for long-term scalability and business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Executive Leadership, Product, Marketing, and Clinical Stakeholders to identify unmet customer and operational needs, translating business goals into technical strategies that deliver outcomes for our patients and clinicians&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Formally and informally mentor senior and junior engineers, fostering a culture of curiosity, humility, and technical excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 10+ years of experience building and scaling complex engineering solutions, with a proven track record of leading large-scale architectural migrations in a startup environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You possess proven production experience in Django/DRF and React/Next.js or similar technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are comfortable operating at a high level of abstraction, translating vague product and growth goals into concrete technical roadmaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You bring a versatile background in building consumer-facing products alongside deep expertise in architecting complex operational and workflow management systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a power-user of agentic coding tools and LLM’s (e.g., Claude Code, GitHub Copilot) to accelerate development and mentor the team on high-leverage prompting and code-auditing strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You help create a respectful, low-ego team environment, approaching discussions with curiosity and humility.&lt;/li&gt;
